BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:CATS: The Jellicle Ball
DTSTART:20260710T230000Z
DTEND:20260711T014500Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T185714Z
UID:982286
DESCRIPTION:<p>Come One\, Come All &ndash\; The Jellicle Cats are having a
  Ball. Based on T.S. Eliot&rsquo\;s <em>Old Possum&rsquo\;s Book of Practi
 cal Cats</em>\, Andrew Lloyd Webber&rsquo\;s worldwide phenomenon <em>CATS
 </em> is reimagined in a production that smashed records\, won awards and 
 left New York City purring. And now <em>CATS: The Jellicle Ball</em> ascen
 ds to Broadway in a kaleidoscope of glittering spectacle\, iconic music an
 d electrifying ballroom choreography that <em>The New York Times</em> call
 s &ldquo\;a lightning strike that sets joy free!&rdquo\;&nbsp\;<br /><br /
 >Broadway meets Runway in the fiercest event of the season\, directed by O
 bie Award winners Zhailon Levingston and Bill Rauch\, with choreography by
  Obie Award winners and New York City Ballroom icons Omari Wiles (House of
  NiNa Oricci) and Arturo Lyons (House of Miyake-Mugler). Don&rsquo\;t miss
  this &ldquo\;sexy celebration of love and resilience&rdquo\; (<em>New Yor
 k Daily News</em>) and &ldquo\;the most exhilarating fun that can be had i
 n the theater&rdquo\; (<em>The Washington Post</em>).<br /><br />&ldquo\;A
  lightning strike. <em>CATS: the Jellicle Ball</em> has managed a Grizabel
 la return\, reincarnating itself in fabulousness. It sets the joy free!&rd
 quo\; &ndash\;Jesse Green\, <em>The New York Times<br /></em><br />&ldquo\
 ;Paris is purring. The fur flies in an absolutely fabulous reconception. L
 evingston and Rauch&rsquo\;s vision fits <em>CATS: The Jellicle Ball</em> 
 like a long sequined glove.&rdquo\; &ndash\;Adam Feldman\, <em>Time Out Ne
 w York</em><br /><br />&ldquo\;This splashy\, jaw-dropping reimagination o
 f Andrew Lloyd Webber&rsquo\;s crowd-pleasing <em>CATS</em> is the most ex
 hilarating fun that can be had in a theater.&rdquo\; &ndash\; Naveen Kumar
 \, <em>The Washington Post</em><br /><br />FIVE STARS -  &ldquo\;A raucous
  success. The most fun you'll have at the theater.&rdquo\; &ndash\;Johnny 
 Oleksinski\, <em>The New York Post</em></p>
LOCATION:Broadhurst Theatre\, 235 West 44th Street\, New York NY 10036
END:VEVENT
